OL,4,CGovernment borrowing fell in April as
OL,5,CUK reopened
OL,6, Government borrowing fell in April
OL,7, compared with the same month last year,
OL,8, as parts of the economy reopened after
OL,9, lockdown measures eased.
OL,11,FBorrowing - the difference between
OL,12,Fspending and tax income - was #31.7bn,
OL,13,Fofficial figures show, which was
OL,14,F#15.6bn lower than April last year.
OL,16,FHowever, the figure was the second
OL,17,Fhighest for April since records began.
OL,19,FBorrowing has been hitting record
OL,20,Flevels with billions being spent on
OL,21,Fmeasures such as furlough payments.
